# Diode Basics

## Overview
A diode is a semiconductor device that allows current to flow in one direction and blocks current in the reverse direction.

## Concepts Covered
- PN junction
- Forward bias
- Reverse bias
- Threshold voltage
- V-I characteristics

## Key Understanding
A silicon diode typically starts conducting after approximately 0.7V in forward bias.

## Automotive and Embedded Relevance
Diodes are used in:
- reverse polarity protection
- rectifier circuits
- signal clipping
- power supply systems

## Common Failure Modes
- overheating
- reverse breakdown
- excessive current damage

## Key Learning
A diode is not an ideal switch. It has nonlinear behavior and threshold voltage characteristics.
